Prompt: Comprehensive Game Design Document - Project "Idle Clone" (W1-W4)Role: You are a Senior Game Developer and Systems Architect. Your goal is to design a multi-character idle MMORPG inspired by Legends of Idleon, covering all mechanics from World 1 to World 4.1. Core Engine & Multi-Character SystemAccount-Wide Progression: Create a "Family" system where all characters share a bank, achievements, and "Account Bonuses".Character Slots: Implement a system where reaching certain total account levels unlocks up to 10 character slots.AFK Gains Logic: Develop a formula to calculate offline progress:$$Gains = Time\_Offline \times Kills/Hr \times Drop\_Rate \times AFK\_Efficiency$$2. World-Specific Mechanics (The Progression Pillars)World 1: The Foundation (Forest/Mining)Smithing: A production system where players use "Anvils" to craft gear. Items require ores, monster drops, and time. Includes a "Production" tab for passive item generation (thread, nails).Stamps: A collection system where flat bonuses (HP, Damage, Skill Speed) are upgraded using coins and materials. Cost increases exponentially.Stat Statues: Permanent buffs earned by handing in stone statues to an NPC.World 2: Complexity & Scaling (Desert/Alchemy)Alchemy: The most critical system.Bubbles: 4 cauldrons (STR, AGI, WIS, LUK) where players "roll" for new bubbles. Bubbles provide massive multiplicative bonuses.Vials: Turning materials into liquid bonuses.Post Office: A daily delivery system where players exchange resources for "Box Points" to upgrade specific character stats.Obols: A grid-based inventory system for circular/square/sparkle shapes that provide minor stat boosts.World 3: Automation & Construction (Ice/Building)Construction: A 3D-printing style mechanic.Buildings: Construct Shrines (buffs in specific maps) and Salt Refineries.3D Printer: Allows players to "sample" a resource (e.g., Copper Ore) and generate it passively without being on that map.Library: A system to reset talent point caps (e.g., taking a skill from level 100 to 145).Worship & Trapping: Two new skills. Worship uses "Totems" for tower-defense style minigames; Trapping involves setting boxes to catch animals over time.World 4: The Meta-Game (Space/Laboratory)Cooking: Using kitchens to discover recipes that give global "Plate" bonuses (Damage, Skill XP).Pet Breeding: A gacha-style system where pets have combat abilities and provide "Spice" for cooking.The Laboratory: Characters must be "uploaded" to a mainframe (effectively going AFK inside a tube) to power up "Nodes" and "Jewels" that double or triple specific bonuses across the whole account.3. Class & Talent SystemBase Classes: Warrior, Archer, Mage, Journeyman.Sub-classes (W2): Barbarian/Squire, Bowman/Hunter, Shaman/Wizard.Elite Classes (W4): Blood Berserker, Divine Knight, Siege Breaker, Beast Master, etc.Talent Trees: Three tabs per character. Tab 1 (Base), Tab 2 (Sub-class), Tab 3 (Elite/Skill-specific).4. Economy & CurrenciesCoinage: 100 Bronze = 1 Silver, 100 Silver = 1 Gold, 100 Gold = 1 Platinum, 100 Platinum = 1 Dementia.Boss Keys: Daily logic where players receive keys to enter boss rooms (Amarok, Efaunt, Chizoar).5. Technical Requirements for OutputData Structure: Use JSON for item databases, monster stats, and quest logs.UI/UX: Describe a "Menu Bar" with: Inventory, Talents, Codex (Quests/Cards), Map, and Quick-Ref (to check Alchemy/Construction from anywhere).Visual Style: 2.5D Side-scrolling, pixel art aesthetic, vibrant colors.
